  "prompt": "why do people like bubble football in UK?",
  "response": "People in the UK enjoy bubble football (or zorb football) for several reasons:\n\n1. Novelty and Fun\n- It's a unique and amusing twist on traditional football\n- Provides a comedic and entertaining experience\n- Allows people to play football in a completely different way\n\n2. Social Activity\n- Great for team building\n- Excellent for group events like stag/hen parties\n- Allows friends to enjoy a fun, shared experience\n\n3. Physical Entertainment\n- Safe way to bump into other players\n- Reduces risk of serious injury compared to regular football\n- Provides physical exercise in a playful manner\n\n4. Excitement and Laughter\n- Players wear inflatable bubbles that cover their upper body\n- Collisions and bouncing around create hilarious moments\n- Generates lots of laughter and enjoyment\n\n5. Suitable for All Skill Levels\n- No need to be a skilled footballer\n- Anyone can participate and have fun\n- Levels the playing field between experienced and novice players\n\n6. Stress Relief\n- Provides a lighthearted way to release tension\n- Allows people to be silly and playful\n- Offers a break from serious everyday activities\n\nThese factors make bubble football an increasingly popular recreational activity in the UK.",
